Comment.MultiLanguageText: How long one comm cycle takes

AttributeList.Text: NOTES: 1. Size of CalcValue: 14 bytes 2. Max size one GET block can do: 222 bytes 3. Max. approx 10 simultaneous GET requests, so broken up into groups 4. Only one group is active per cycle. Total update cycle time is (Groups * OB31 cycle time) 5. REQ must stay high until the GET has completed (level signal). An edge on REQ will not work. 6. When a GET has completed it raises NDR for one cycle. The whole group is complete when all NDRs have been raised. GETs in the same group may not complete in the same cycle, so each NDR is used to SET a bit in xGroup to prevent retriggering while waiting (and thus getting stuck in that group as the NDRs will never go high at the same time). This is actually a sign that the OB cyclic rate is faster than the communication runs (two or more cycles per group) and that it should be increased, but at least it doesn't get stuck. 7. More groups can be added by following the model. WARNING: don't play here unless you are prepared for the consequences :-)
